  "description": "Erection of single storey rear and two storey side extensions",
  "decision_date": "12/12/2022",
  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposed two storey side extension, due to its design, scale and siting would result in a disproportionate and visually incongruous addition that would fail to harmonise with the architectural composition of the original dwelling and would read as a discordant and intrusive form of development on this prominent corner plot, to the detriment of the appearance of the subject dwelling, the visual amenities of the street scene and the character of the area. The proposal is therefore contrary to Policy BE1 of the Hillingdon Local Plan: Part One - Strategic Policies (November 2012), Policies DMHB 11, DMHB 12 and DMHD 1 of the Hillingdon Local Plan: Part Two - Development Management Policies (January 2020), Policy D3 of the London Plan (2021) and Section 12 of the National Planning Policy Framework (2021)."
